main event: A bright light was observed in the sky from a Coast Guard ship in the Pacific Ocean on November 29, 1964.
interesting points: The light was observed for a duration of 1 to 2 minutes, moving at 330 degrees true.
The light was unlikely to be an atmospheric phenomenon, celestial body, weather balloon, or other aircraft.
The observation was made from a Coast Guard ship in the Pacific Ocean.
The weather conditions were described as having large swells and being cloudy.
The light was observed at a high position angle of 25 degrees.
sighted object: a bright light in the sky
witnesses: military personnel on a Coast Guard ship
